			<ns0:name>MerwanWi...@gmail.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/115470306379614629362/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I fixed the problem. I did not  have NACL_SDK_ROOT set.

I believe the messaging should be updated when this is the case. As it's not very obvious that the install is incomplete without setting the environment variable.

Without NACL_SDK_ROOT:
python init_project.py -d ../examples -n hello_tutorial
init_project parsing its arguments.
init_project is preparing your project.
exceptions must be old-style classes or derived from BaseException, not NoneType

With NACL_SDK_ROOT:
python init_project.py -d ../examples -n hello_tutorial
init_project parsing its arguments.
init_project is preparing your project.
init_project has copied the appropriate files to: ../examples/hello_tutorial
init_project has prepared ../examples/hello_tutorial/build.scons.
init_project has prepared ../examples/hello_tutorial/hello_tutorial.cc.
init_project has prepared ../examples/hello_tutorial/hello_tutorial.html.
init_project has prepared ../examples/hello_tutorial/scons.
